Since there are multiple places in Salesforce instance which require a configuration, in the Setup Overview page you can find all the links necessary for the configuration.

## User permissions
- In the Application collection, search for Doxee Setup:&nbsp;![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- After entering the Doxee Setup app, we land in the Setup Overview, where direct links are provided for the most important Configuration Settings of the Doxee App for Salesforce.&nbsp;![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

### Permission Sets
**Permission sets **are a collection of sets that are created during the app installation. These need to be assigned to the corresponding user. 

The system administrator has access to all features of the package. 

- **Doxee Setup and Administration** Permission set needs to be assigned to a particular user, who requires access to all features of the Doxee App for Salesforce.

- **Doxee Connector User*** *Permission set is assigned to users who require access to *Doxee Composer and Doxee Workplace Components*. 

- **Doxee Business Designer **Permission set is assigned to users who require access to the *Doxee Business Designer Component.*

- **Doxee Business Designer User **Permission set is assigned to users who will create templates inside the Business Designer.

### Assigning Permission Sets to Users
Assigning permission sets can be done in two ways:

- Inside Permission Sets, select a single permission set (the above mentioned) 

and click **Manage Assignments**:

![A screenshot of a computer screen  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click **Add Assignments** 🡪 select desired Users and click **Assign**.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Search for a specific user and scroll until Permission Set section:

![A white rectangular object with a blue border  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click **Edit Assignments** and assign all permission sets this user requires. 

For more information see, [Documentation on Permission Sets](https://help.salesforce.com/articleView?id=perm_sets_overview.htm&amp;type=5).

**Hint**: The Permission Set for “Doxee Connector User” controls whether a user can access the component which was inserted by the means of the Doxee Lightning component. However, it does not control whether a user is able to access the tasks of the Doxee Workplace process. For this it is necessary to add the user also to the corresponding group as explained below in the “Public Groups” section.

### Public Groups
Back to Setup Overview page (see chapter [Configuration](#_Configuration)), the next section is Public Groups. Please review all the public groups and decide which user should be assigned to what group, based on the user role in the Doxee App for Salesforce. For assigning the public groups, please go to direct link **Public Groups**:

![Ein Bild, das Text enthält.  Automatisch generierte Beschreibung](data:image/png;base64,)

Select a desired Public Group, click **Edit**, in the dropdown **Search**, choose **Users**, and under **Available Members**, find the desired user, click **Add** and then **Save** to complete the Assignment. 

**Important note regarding setup**: Currently it is required that users who should log-in to Doxee Workplace need to have some group assigned at Salesforce.

**Additional note**: In case the existing processes get modified or additional processes get created and certain steps within these processes are assigned to different groups you need to make sure that the users are assigned to those groups.

## Custom Settings
The next step inside the Setup Overview (see chapter [Configuration](#_Configuration)) is to create links from the AWS instance (the domain of your choosing) and all the Doxee applications that need to be set as URLs. In the Setup Overview page, under Custom Setting: Doxee Settings, click **Edit **and edit the following form fields:

**Administrator Contact Email**, set the Email of the contact person.

**Process End URL**, if this link is during the installation not known, you can skip this form field and fill it out once the process is in place and the final step of the process is defined (skipping to some Salesforce Page). 

**Business Designer Server Address: **Define the domain name you want to use. Remember that this domain does not exist yet, it is about to be created and the domain name you define will be used for AWS instance creation. 

The naming convention is **{Desired Name}.cloud.infinica.com**. The links of applications will adjust accordingly. The form fields that have prefilled Doxee Application URLs do not need to be filled, unless advised otherwise: 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

## Connected App
The next configuration step is the creation of a connected App. Follow the link from the Overview Setup page **Connected Apps**.

- &nbsp;![Ein Bild, das Text enthält.  Automatisch generierte Beschreibung](data:image/jpeg;base64,)Click **New Connected App** in the right upper corner. 

- Fill out the form fields of the **Basic Information** section accordingly. &nbsp;![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Inside the **API (Enable OAuth Settings)** click the checkbox: **Enable OAuth Settings. **Under the Callback URL please fill out the following link, considering your newly created domain name. Define Callback URL - after successful authentication by Salesforce, redirect to this URL will be done.

For Doxee Business Designer, Doxee Process Designer, and Doxee Resource Explorer access: http://localhost/infinica/auth

- For Doxee Workplace: https://&lt;infinicahost&gt;/infinica-workplace/login.hbs

- For Doxee Business Designer it is https://&lt;infinicahost&gt;/infinica-business- designer/login

- For Doxee Content Repository: https://&lt;infinicahost&gt;/infinica-content- repository/

- You need to define which OAuth Scope of Salesforce will be needed by Doxee Workplace. From the Available OAuth Scopes select following:

Access the identity URL service

- Access unique user identifiers

- Manage user data via APIs

- Perform requests at any time

- Uncheck ‘Require Proof Key for Code Exchange (PKCE)’ even if it’s checked per default.

- Check ‘Require Secret for Refresh Token Flow’ &amp; ‘Enable Authorization Code and Credentials Flow’.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Check Require Secret for Web Server Flow

- Check Introspect all tokens.

After saving you be able to reveal Consumer Key and Consumer secret under **Manage Consumer Details** (requires additional Salesforce authentication).

Please copy these two items and paste them inside the Setup XML file which you can download from the Overview Setup page:

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

**Once you have downloaded the Setup XML and copied the Consumer Key and Consumer Secret into corresponding nodes of the XML, please send the XML file to Doxee contact person. **

Note: In case a new Salesforce instance (e.g. sandbox) gets created you must send the new Consumer Key and Consumer Secret to Doxee in case you want to connect your Doxee Server with that newly generated Salesforce instance.
